.TH PODSOCK 1 "2026-07-01" "podsock 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podsock \- podman wrapper with shorthand +flags for host integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podsock
[+\fIflags\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs...\fR]
.br
.B podsock
help [\fIcommand\fR]
.br
.B podsock
\fB--version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Podsock is a wrapper around
.BR podman (1)
that adds convenient shorthand flags (e.g.,
.BR +t ,
.BR +w ,
.BR +D )
for common host-integration patterns: terminal interactivity, Wayland display
forwarding, SSH agent forwarding, GPU access, audio forwarding, network
capabilities, debug capabilities, FUSE support, desktop app registration, and
XDG Desktop Portal access.
.PP
Podsock does not hide the underlying podman CLI. All standard podman subcommands
and options pass through unchanged. The wrapper only intercepts
.B +flags
(prefixed with
.BR + )
and the
.BR shell ,
.BR helm ,
and
.BR cleanup
subcommands.
.SH +FLAGS
Flags are prefixed with
.B +
and can be chained:
.B +Tdn
gives terminal, debug, and network.
.TP
.B +t
Terminal interactivity (uses
.BR $TERM )
.TP
.B +T
Terminal interactivity (forces
.BR xterm-256color )
.TP
.B +w
Wayland display forwarding
.TP
.B +s
SSH agent socket forwarding
.TP
.B +g
GPU/graphics device access (
.BR /dev/dri )
.TP
.B +p
PipeWire playback-only audio forwarding
.TP
.B +P
PipeWire full audio forwarding (playback + capture)
.TP
.B +n
Host network with extra capabilities
.TP
.B +d
Debug capabilities (ptrace, perfmon)
.TP
.B +A
Register as desktop app (creates
.B .desktop
launcher)
.TP
.B +D
Enable XDG Desktop Portal access (implies
.BR +A ,
filtered D-Bus)
.TP
.B +f
FUSE filesystem support (e.g., sshfs)
.TP
.B +?
Dry run (print the podman command without executing)
.PP
The
.B +t
and
.B +T
flags are mutually exclusive.
The
.B +p
and
.B +P
flags are mutually exclusive.
.B +t ,
.BR +T ,
.BR +w ,
.BR +s ,
.BR +g ,
.BR +p ,
.BR +P ,
.BR +n ,
.BR +d ,
.BR +A ,
.BR +D ,
and
.B +f
are only supported with the
.B run
and
.B create
subcommands.
.B +?
is supported with all subcommands.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
In addition to all standard podman subcommands, podsock provides:
.TP
.B shell <container> [command]
Run an interactive shell (or command) in a running container via
.BR "podman exec" .
Defaults to
.B bash
if no command is given.
.TP
.B helm <container>
Start an existing container interactively via
.BR "podman start" .
If the container was created with
.B +A
or
.BR +D ,
ensures the
.B .desktop
file and D-Bus proxy are ready.
.TP
.B cleanup
Clean up stale D-Bus proxies and
.B .desktop
files for deleted containers. Running containers are left untouched. Stopped
containers have their proxy stopped. Fully removed (orphan) containers have
both their proxy directories and
.B .desktop
files cleaned up.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B podsock run +Twg --rm -it ubuntu bash
Run an Ubuntu container with terminal, Wayland, and GPU access.
.TP
.B podsock run +p --rm -it myimage
Run with playback-only PipeWire audio forwarding.
.TP
.B podsock run +D --name=myapp myimage
Run with XDG Desktop Portal access and desktop app registration.
.TP
.B podsock run +Tfs --rm -it myimage
Run with terminal, FUSE support, and SSH agent forwarding.
.TP
.B podsock +? run +Tngd myimage
Dry run: print the equivalent podman command without executing.
.TP
.B podsock shell mycontainer
Open a bash shell in a running container.
.TP
.B podsock shell mycontainer python
Run python in a running container.
.TP
.B podsock helm mycontainer
Start a container interactively.
.TP
.B podsock cleanup
Clean up stale D-Bus proxies and orphaned .desktop files.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PODSOCK_INIT
Set to
.B 0
to disable the
.B --init
flag that podsock adds by default. Default:
.BR 1 .
.TP
.B PODSOCK_RTDIR
Override the runtime directory used for socket paths. Default:
.BR /run/user/<uid> .
.TP
.B PODSOCK_DRYRUN
Set to
.B 1
to force dry-run mode (equivalent to
.BR +? ).
.TP
.B PODSOCK_DATADIR
Override the directory where podsock looks for data files (PipeWire configs).
.TP
.B TERM
Used by
.B +t
for the container's
.B $TERM
environment variable.
.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
Used by
.B +w
for Wayland socket forwarding.
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Used by
.BR +w ,
.BR +p ,
.B +P
for socket paths.
.TP
.B SSH_AUTH_SOCK
Used by
.B +s
for SSH agent forwarding.
.TP
.B DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS
Used by
.B +D
for the D-Bus proxy. Must be a
.B unix:
address.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.var/podsock/sockets/
Persistent proxy socket directories for
.B +D
containers.
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/applications/podsock_*.desktop
Desktop launchers created by
.B +A
and
.BR +D .
.TP
.B ~/.config/pipewire/pipewire.conf.d/99-podsock-playback.conf
PipeWire config auto-installed by
.B +p
on first use.
.TP
.B ~/.config/wireplumber/wireplumber.conf.d/99-podsock-playback-only.conf
WirePlumber config auto-installed by
.B +p
on first use.
.SH WARNINGS
Podsock always disables SELinux labeling
.RB ( --security-opt\ label=disable )
and shares the host user's UID and username with the container
.RB ( --userns\ keep-id ).
.PP
.B +D
does NOT filter individual portal interfaces. Access control is delegated to
the desktop environment's permission dialogs. Treat untrusted apps with
.B +D
with the same caution as a Flatpak with full portal access.
.PP
.B +f
grants
.BR CAP_SYS_ADMIN ,
one of the most powerful Linux capabilities. In addition to FUSE mounts,
SYS_ADMIN enables a broad range of privileged operations (mount/umount,
namespace manipulation, various sysadmin actions). Only use
.B +f
with trusted container images.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR podman (1),
.BR podman-run (1),
.BR podman-exec (1),
.BR podman-start (1),
.BR xdg-dbus-proxy (1),
.BR pipewire (1)
.SH BUGS
See
.B KNOWN_ISSUES.md
in the source repository for known limitations, including the FUSE document
portal issue that affects
.B +D
on systems where
.I /run/user/<uid>/doc
is a FUSE mount.
